    "Extended Summary": {
      "children": [
        {
          "data": {
            "inline": [
              {
                "data": {
                  "value": "DAISY is a feature descriptor similar to SIFT formulated in a way that allows for fast dense extraction. Typically, this is practical for bag-of-features image representations."
                },
                "type": "Words"
              }
            ],
            "inner": []
          },
          "type": "Paragraph"
        },
        {
          "data": {
            "inline": [
              {
                "data": {
                  "value": "The implementation follows Tola et al.  but deviate on the following points:"
                },
                "type": "Words"
              }
            ],
            "inner": []
          },
          "type": "Paragraph"
        },
        {
          "data": {
            "value": [
              "* Histogram bin contribution are smoothed with a circular Gaussian",
              "  window over the tonal range (the angular range).",
              "* The sigma values of the spatial Gaussian smoothing in this code do not",
              "  match the sigma values in the original code by Tola et al. [2]_. In",
              "  their code, spatial smoothing is applied to both the input image and",
              "  the center histogram. However, this smoothing is not documented in [1]_",
              "  and, therefore, it is omitted."
            ]
          },
          "type": "BlockQuote"
        }
      ],
      "title": null
    },
